[{"id":"FT549161","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"Let <em>T</em> be the triangular region bounded by l , the <em>x</em>-axis, and the line <em>x</em>=1. Show that the area of <em>T</em> is 1/2n.","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"A graph plots a curve and a line. The graph of y equals x to the n power is a concave upward increasing curve that begins at the origin levels off along the x axis, and further rises to the point 1 comma 1. A vertical line from the x axis is drawn to the point 1 comma 1. A line l originates from the x axis between the curve and the vertical line. The line rises to the right with a negative slope to the point 1 comma 1. The region above the x axis bounded by the curve and the line l is labeled S. The region above the x axis bounded by the line l and the vertical line is labeled T. All values estimated.\" height=\"230\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/0579732b8e933fdae24c77dda8b7607f/original.png\" width=\"250\" /></p>\n\n<p>Let <span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Mistral\">l </span></span> be the line tangent to the graph of <em> y </em> = <em> x <sup> n </sup> </em> at the point (1, 1), where <em> n </em> &gt;1, as shown above.</p>\n"}]}]